\": \"C\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Software engineering is especially suitable for ___ projects.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Toy scripts\",\n            \"Single-use macros\",\n            \"Large software systems\",\n            \"One-line utilities\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"C\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"What does SDLC stand for?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Software Design Logical Cycle\",\n            \"System Development Lifecycle\",\n            \"Software Development Life Cycle\",\n            \"Structured Development Life Cycle\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"C\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"What is the primary goal of SDLC?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Deliver high-quality, maintainable software that meets user requirements\",\n            \"Reduce software size\",\n            \"Minimize testing\",\n            \"Avoid documentation\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"A\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Which stage comes first in the SDLC?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Design\",\n            \"Planning and Requirement Analysis\",\n            \"Testing\",\n            \"Deployment\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Which of the following is NOT a stage of SDLC as per the article?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Planning and Requirement Analysis\",\n            \"Design\",\n            \"Development\",\n            \"Retirement\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"D\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"SDLC is described as a methodology that defines the procedure of software development ____.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"step-by-step\",\n            \"ad-hoc\",\n            \"improvisational\",\n            \"unsystematic\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"A\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"SDLC specifies tasks to be performed at various stages by ____.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"project managers only\",\n            \"a marketing team\",\n            \"software engineers or developers\",\n            \"end users\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"C\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"One key benefit of SDLC is that it ensures the end product meets the customer\'s ____.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"expectations and fits within the budget\",\n            \"design preferences\",\n            \"development team\'s convenience\",\n            \"latest UI trends\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"A\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"SDLC provides a precise plan describing how to develop, maintain, replace, and ____ software.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"license\",\n            \"discontinue\",\n            \"enhance\",\n            \"market\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"C\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"What is emphasized at every stage of SDLC according to the conceptual model?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Risk management\",\n            \"Marketing strategy\",\n            \"Customer incentives\",\n            \"Sales forecasting\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"A\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Which SDLC methodology emphasizes sequential stages like planning, design, testing, deployment, and maintenance?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Agile\",\n            \"Waterfall\",\n            \"Kanban\",\n            \"Lean\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Which SDLC models are listed as top models in one of the related articles?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"DevOps, Lean, XP, Spiral, Agile\",\n            \"Agile, Waterfall, Spiral, Iterative, V-Shaped\",\n            \"Scrum, XP, Lean, Kanban, RAD\",\n            \"Waterfall, XP, Spiral, DevOps, Crystal\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Which model combines iterative development with risk management?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Waterfall\",\n            \"V-Model\",\n            \"Spiral\",\n            \"Prototyping\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"C\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"SDLC is a model followed by many ____ organizations to develop software.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"marketing\",\n            \"software development\",\n            \"financial\",\n            \"logistics\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"According to AWS, SDLC helps minimize project ____ through forward planning.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"size\",\n            \"risks\",\n            \"users\",\n            \"documentation\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Which of the following is a framework used to structure software development life cycle?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"SDLC\",\n            \"HTML\",\n            \"HTTP\",\n            \"JSON\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"A\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Which SDLC stage focuses on gathering customer inputs and conducting market surveys?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Requirement Analysis\",\n            \"Design\",\n            \"Deployment\",\n            \"Testing\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"A\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Which phase of the Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) focuses on defining detailed functional and non-functional requirements?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Planning\",\n            \"Requirements Analysis\",\n            \"Implementation\",\n            \"Testing\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"SDLC divides the software design process into ____ parts.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"few\",\n            \"small\",\n            \"unrelated\",\n            \"excessive\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"SDLC ensures delivery of ____ software as per the article.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"inefficient\",\n            \"high-quality, maintainable\",\n            \"expensive\",\n            \"temporary\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"The SDLC provides a structured process to design, develop, and ____ software.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"distribute\",\n            \"test\",\n            \"sell\",\n            \"archive\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Which of the following is **not** explicitly mentioned as a key factor of software quality in the article?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Portability\",\n            \"Usability\",\n            \"Correctness\",\n            \"Scalability\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"D\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Software quality ensures a product is reliable, maintainable, and ___.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"User-friendly\",\n            \"Expensive\",\n            \"Complex\",\n            \"Outdated\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"A\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Software quality goes beyond just meeting ___.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Deadlines\",\n            \"Requirements\",\n            \"Budgets\",\n            \"User feedback\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Which of these is **not** listed in the article\'s conclusion?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Efficiency\",\n            \"Correctness\",\n            \"Portability\",\n            \"Marketability\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"D\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"A robust quality management system and continuous improvement processes help achieve ___ standards.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Financial\",\n            \"Operational\",\n            \"Quality\",\n            \"Marketing\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"C\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"High-quality software is described as functional, efficient, and ___.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Adaptable to user needs\",\n            \"Expensive\",\n            \"Proprietary\",\n            \"Obsolete\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"A\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Software quality involves key factors like portability, usability, correctness, and ___.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Efficiency\",\n            \"Security\",\n            \"Popularity\",\n            \"Cost\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"A\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Which characteristic of good software includes functionality, usability, reliability, performance, and security?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Software Quality\",\n            \"Software Characteristics\",\n            \"Software Requirements\",\n            \"Software Documentation\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"According to GeeksforGeeks, good software meets user needs, performs reliably, and is ___.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Easy to maintain\",\n            \"Hard to reproduce\",\n            \"Expensive to run\",\n            \"Technically deep\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"A\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Which of the following is **not** typically included in characteristics of good software?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Testability\",\n            \"Scalability\",\n            \"Maintainability\",\n            \"Randomness\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"D\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"What does Quality Assurance (QA) focus on according to GeeksforGeeks?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Preventing defects by ensuring proper processes are followed\",\n            \"Fixing defects after development ends\",\n            \"Marketing software quality\",\n            \"Ignoring development standards\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"A\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Quality Control (QC) is primarily concerned with ___.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Implementing development standards\",\n            \"Identifying and fixing defects after development\",\n            \"Defining quality policies\",\n            \"Preventing process errors\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Which activity runs parallel to Software Development and ensures processes are implemented correctly?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Software Marketing\",\n            \"Software Quality Assurance (SQA)\",\n            \"Database Management\",\n            \"User Experience Design\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"SQA is described as an umbrella activity that is applied ___ the software process.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"At the end of\",\n            \"Parallel to\",\n            \"Before\",\n            \"After deployment of\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Quality planning involves identifying and incorporating relevant quality ___.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Standards into product and processes\",\n            \"Cost estimates\",\n            \"Marketing strategies\",\n            \"User training\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"A\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"What is the main goal of a Software Quality Assurance Plan?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Guarantee the product is trouble- and bug-free\",\n            \"Improve UI design aesthetics\",\n            \"Reduce software licensing costs\",\n            \"Optimize network traffic\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"A\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"A Software Quality Assurance Plan determines QA duties, areas for review, and ___.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Work products for SQA\",\n            \"Budget allocations\",\n            \"Marketing campaigns\",\n            \"End-user surveys\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"A\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Software quality describes the degree to which components meet specified requirements and ___.\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Developer convenience\",\n            \"User or customer needs\",\n            \"Hardware constraints\",\n            \"Last-minute changes\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"Which of the following best describes software engineering?\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"Writing code without documentation\",\n            \"A systematic, disciplined, and quantifiable approach to software development\",\n            \"Installing and configuring hardware\",\n            \"Debugging programs only\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    },\n    {\n        \"question\": \"What is the pin to the admin panel\",\n        \"options\": [\n            \"4224\",\n            \"1245\",\n            \"1337\",\n            \"8008\"\n        ],\n        \"answer\": \"B\"\n    }\n]');

